Since 2020-02-28, healpix configure script works properly with "-L" and "--auto" set together.
This patch modifies configure script to pretend accepting standard "--prefix XXXX" option, letting
us go with standard ConfigureMake easyblock.  
(finally) avoiding interactive Q&A mode of configure script breaking every then and now.

Josef Dvoracek | Institute of Physics | Czech Academy of Sciences | 2020-11-16


diff -Nru Healpix_3.70_orig/configure Healpix_3.70/configure
--- Healpix_3.70.orig/configure	2020-11-16 21:14:16.180338000 +0100
+++ Healpix_3.70/configure	2020-11-16 21:15:38.959970000 +0100
@@ -177,6 +177,9 @@
         HPX_CONF_DIR=${HPX_CONF_DIR_INPLACE}
         INTERACTIVE=0
 	;;
+      --prefix=*)
+        echo "pretend that configure script accepts --prefix to behave as configuremake expects.."
+        ;;
       *)
         echo "Unknown option: $i"
 	echoLn "\n${usage}\n\n${usage2}\n\n"
